---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card.astro';
import CtaBlock from '../components/CtaBlock.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Revenue Architects"
  description="Revenue Architects is the practitioner team that created and stewards RAOS — the Revenue Architecture Operating System. We certify practitioners, train teams, and take the engagements where the architecture has to hold."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="border-b border-navy-100">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal">
        The firm behind Revenue Architecture&reg;
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-prose text-4xl leading-tight md:text-5xl">
        We don&rsquo;t just design your revenue architecture. We operate it.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-prose text-lg text-ink">
        Revenue Architects is the practitioner team that created and stewards RAOS — the
        Revenue Architecture Operating System. We certify the practitioners, train the
        teams, and take on the engagements where the architecture has to hold.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row">
        <a
          href="/engage"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-card bg-orange px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-surface transition-colors hover:bg-orange-600"
        >
          Engage the authors
        </a>
        <a
          href="/services#certification"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-card border border-navy px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-navy transition-colors hover:bg-navy hover:text-surface"
        >
          Get certified
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Authority cue -->
  <section class="bg-navy-100/40">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-10">
      <p class="max-w-prose text-base text-navy">
        We hold the Revenue Architecture&reg; trademark and the canon behind it: three
        layers, nine playbooks, twenty-seven plays, five Operating Agents.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://revenuearchitecture.com"
        rel="noopener"
        target="_blank"
        class="mt-3 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-teal transition-colors hover:text-teal-600"
      >
        See the full method at revenuearchitecture.com &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Three service cards -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-section">
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl">Three ways to work with the source</h2>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-prose text-ink">
      The same team that wrote the method delivers all three. Most firms start with
      Certification or an Engagement.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <Card
        title="Certification"
        eyebrow="Foreground"
        accent="orange"
        href="/services#certification"
        cta="Become certified"
      >
        Become a Certified Revenue Architect™. License the method, get the skill files
        and badge, and deploy with bench support behind you.
      </Card>
      <Card title="Training" eyebrow="Enablement" accent="teal" href="/services#training" cta="See training">
        Train-the-trainer and team enablement on RAOS for in-house revenue
        organizations and agencies.
      </Card>
      <Card
        title="Engagement"
        eyebrow="Foreground"
        accent="orange"
        href="/services#engagement"
        cta="Scope an engagement"
      >
        The authors design and operate your revenue architecture — advisory-led or
        done-with-you. A limited number of slots.
      </Card>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The authors -->
  <section class="bg-navy-100/40">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-section">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal">The authors</p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl md:text-3xl">You are hiring the source.</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 max-w-prose space-y-4 text-ink">
        <p>
          Sherwin and John wrote the method. They lead every engagement we take, backed
          by a supporting team and a network of Certified Architects who carry the same
          standard into the field.
        </p>
        <p>
          We take a small number of engagements at a time. That is by design. The people
          who built the architecture are the people who run it with you — not a junior
          bench, not a licensee, not a loose interpretation of the words.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a
        href="/about"
        class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-semibold text-orange transition-colors hover:text-orange-600"
      >
        Meet the firm &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FACT Intake teaser -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-content px-6 py-section">
    <div class="rounded-card border border-dashed border-teal-300 bg-teal-100/40 p-8">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-teal-600">
        Coming soon — phase 2
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-2xl text-teal-900 md:text-3xl">
        Talk to the Engagement Agent
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-prose text-ink">
        The method, run on you, before you&rsquo;ve paid a dollar. An agentic scoping
        conversation is launching soon. Until then, reach the authors directly.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/engage"
        class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-card border border-teal px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-teal transition-colors hover:bg-teal hover:text-surface"
      >
        Start with Engage
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Two-door close -->
  <CtaBlock
    eyebrow="Two ways forward"
    heading="Read the method, or scope an engagement with the authors."
    body="Run the Diagnostic and read the canon at revenuearchitecture.com — or bring us a problem and we will tell you whether it is one we should take."
    buttons={[
      { href: 'https://revenuearchitecture.com', label: 'Read the method', variant: 'teal', external: true },
      { href: '/engage', label: 'Scope an engagement', variant: 'orange' },
    ]}
  />
</Base>
